main event: A resident of Hamburg, New York reported sighting a brilliantly lighted unidentified flying object over the Hamburg area on February 7, 1969.
interesting points: The object was described as round in shape, approximately 40-50 feet in diameter, and emitting a brilliant white light.
The object was reported to be hovering and maneuvering at an estimated altitude of 1,000-2,000 feet.
No sound was heard associated with the object.
The sighting lasted for approximately 10 minutes.
The United States Air Force, Project Blue Book, classified this sighting as 'Unidentified'.
sighted object: A round, white, brilliantly lighted unidentified flying object
witnesses: Several citizens of Hamburg, New York
